@chaestival_ is back with another record, and it’s her most vulnerable yet. The K-pop soloist and former member of IZ*ONE just dropped her 4th mini album, ‘Till I Die,’ in a uniquely delicate output. This is more than just an exploration of her performance skills, but marks a defining new chapter for the artist, where she fully explores her artistic identity through both song and dance.
We caught up with Chaeyeon to hear about her new release and varied influences from hip hop and R&B to dance pop. Head to the link in bio to read the full interview.
